   /// Create a char KeyCode from a Unicode codepoint.\n    pub fn fromChar(c: u21) KeyCode {\n        return .{ .char = c };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a function key KeyCode (F1-F12).\n    /// Returns null if n is not in range 1-12.\n    pub fn fromF(n: u8) ?KeyCode {\n        if (n >= 1 and n <= 12) {\n            return .{ .f = n };\n        }\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is a printable character.\n    pub fn isChar(self: KeyCode) bool {\n        return self == .char;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is an arrow key.\n    pub fn isArrow(self: KeyCode) bool {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .up, .down, .left, .right => true,\n            else => false,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is a navigation key (arrows, home, end, page up/down).\n    pub fn isNavigation(self: KeyCode) bool {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .up, .down, .left, .right, .home, .end, .page_up, .page_down => true,\n            else => false,\n        };\n    }\n};\n\n/// Modifier key state (ctrl, alt, shift).\npub const Modifiers = packed struct {\n    ctrl: bool = false,\n    alt: bool = false,\n    shift: bool = false,\n    _padding: u5 = 0,\n\n    /// No modifiers pressed.\n    pub const none: Modifiers = .{};\n\n    /// Create modifiers with only ctrl.\n    pub fn ctrl_only() Modifiers {\n        return .{ .ctrl = true };\n    }\n\n    /// }\n};\n\n/// Mouse event kind.\npub const MouseKind = enum {\n    down,\n    up,\n    drag,\n    move,\n    scroll_up,\n    scroll_down,\n\n    /// Check if this is a click event (down or up).\n    pub fn isClick(self: MouseKind) bool {\n        return self == .down or self == .up;\n    }\n\n    /// Check if this is a scroll event.\n    pub fn isScroll(self: MouseKind) bool {\n        return Coordinates increase right and down.\npub const Rect = struct {\n    x: u16,\n    y: u16,\n    width: u16,\n    height: u16,\n\n    pub fn init(x: u16, y: u16, width: u16, height: u16) Rect {\n        return .{ .x = x, .y = y, .width = width, .height = height };\n    }\n\n    /// Returns a new Rect inset by `margin` on all sides.\n    /// Uses saturating subtraction to prevent underflow.\n    /// Position shifts inward; dimensions shrink by 2*margin (or to zero).\n    pub fn inner(self: Rect, margin: u16) Rect {\n        const double_margin = @as(u32, margin) * 2;\n\n        return .{\n            .x = self.x +| margin,\n            .y = self.y +| margin,\n            .width = if (double_margin >= self.width) 0 else self.width - @as(u16, @intCast(double_margin)),\n            .height = if (double_margin >= self.height) 0 else self.height - @as(u16, @intCast(double_margin)),\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Returns area (width * height) as u32 to prevent overflow.\n    pub fn area(self: Rect) u32 {\n        return @as(u32, self.width) * @as(u32, self.height);\n    }\n\n    /// Returns true if rect has zero area.\n    pub fn isEmpty(self: Rect) bool {\n        return self.width == 0 or self.height == 0;\n    }\n\n    /// Clamp a point to be within this rect (inclusive of boundaries).\n    /// Returns the closest point inside the rect.\n    pub fn clamp(self: Rect, x: u16, y: u16) Position {\n        const max_x = self.x +| (self.width -| 1);\n        const max_y = self.y +| (self.height -| 1);\n\n        return .{\n            .x = std.math.clamp(x, self.x, max_x),\n            .y = std.math.clamp(y, self.y, max_y),\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Returns the right edge x coordinate (exclusive).\n    pub fn right(self: Rect) u16 {\n        return self.x +| self.width;\n    }\n\n    /// Returns the bottom edge y coordinate (exclusive).\n    pub fn bottom(self: Rect) u16 {\n        return self.y +| self.height;\n    }\n\n    /// Returns true if the given point is within this rect (inclusive).\n    pub fn contains(self: Rect, x: u16, y: u16) bool {\n        return x >= self.x and\n            x < self.right() and\n            y >= self.y and\n            y < self.bottom();\n    }\n};\n\n// ============================================================\n// SANITY TESTS - Basic functionality\n// ============================================================\n\ntest \"sanity: Position init\" {\n    const pos = Position.init(10, 20);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 10), pos.x);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 20), pos.y);\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Rect init\" {\n    const rect = Rect.init(5, 10, 100, 50);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 5), rect.x);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 10), rect.y);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 100), rect.width);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 50), rect.height);\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Rect area calculation\" {\n    const rect = Rect.init(0, 0, 80, 24);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u32, 1920), rect.area());\n}\n\ntest \"sanity: Rect isEmpty\" {\n    const normal = Rect.init(0, 0, 10, 10);\n    const zero_width = Rect.init(0, 0, 0, 10);\n    const zero_height = Rect.init(0, 0, 10, 0);\n    const zero_both = Rect.init(0, 0, 0, 0);\n\n    try std.testing.expect(!normal.isEmpty());\n    try std.testing.expect(zero_width.isEmpty());\n    try std.testing.expect(zero_height.isEmpty());\n    try std.testing.expect(zero_both.isEmpty());\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// BEHAVIOR TESTS - Document edge cases\n// ============================================================\n\ntest \"behavior: Rect.inner with normal margin\" {\n    const rect = Rect.init(10, 20, 100, 50);\n    const inner_rect = rect.inner(5);\n\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 15), inner_rect.x);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 25), inner_rect.y);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 90), inner_rect.width);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 40), inner_rect.height);\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Rect.inner with margin larger than dimensions returns zero-size rect\" {\n    const rect = Rect.init(10, 10, 5, 5);\n    const inner_rect = rect.inner(10);\n\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 0), inner_rect.width);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 0), inner_rect.height);\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Rect.inner with margin equal to half dimension returns zero-size\" {\n    const rect = Rect.init(0, 0, 10, 10);\n    const inner_rect = rect.inner(5);\n\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 0), inner_rect.width);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 0), inner_rect.height);\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Rect.clamp constrains point to boundaries\" {\n    const rect = Rect.init(10, 20, 100, 50);\n\n    const inside = rect.clamp(50, 40);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 50), inside.x);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 40), inside.y);\n\n    const left = rect.clamp(0, 40);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 10), left.x);\n\n    const top = rect.clamp(50, 0);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 20), top.y);\n\n    const right = rect.clamp(200, 40);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 109), right.x);\n\n    const bottom = rect.clamp(50, 100);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 69), bottom.y);\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Rect.contains checks point membership\" {\n    const rect = Rect.init(10, 20, 100, 50);\n\n    try std.testing.expect(rect.contains(10, 20));\n    try std.testing.expect(rect.contains(50, 40));\n    try std.testing.expect(rect.contains(109, 69));\n\n    try std.testing.expect(!rect.contains(9, 20));\n    try std.testing.expect(!rect.contains(10, 19));\n    try std.testing.expect(!rect.contains(110, 40));\n    try std.testing.expect(!rect.contains(50, 70));\n}\n\ntest \"behavior: Rect.right and Rect.bottom\" {\n    const rect = Rect.init(10, 20, 100, 50);\n\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 110), rect.right());\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 70), rect.bottom());\n}\n\n// ============================================================\n// REGRESSION TESTS - Overflow protection\n// ============================================================\n\ntest \"regression: area calculation does not overflow\" {\n    const rect = Rect.init(0, 0, 65535, 65535);\n    const area_val = rect.area();\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u32, 4294836225), area_val);\n}\n\ntest \"regression: saturating operations prevent underflow/overflow\" {\n    const rect = Rect.init(65535, 65535, 10, 10);\n    const inner_rect = rect.inner(2);\n\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 65535), inner_rect.x);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 65535), inner_rect.y);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 6), inner_rect.width);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 6), inner_rect.height);\n}\n","numLines":208,"startLine":1,"totalLines":208}}}

Flex constraints (flex): Distribute remaining space proportionally\n///\n/// When space is insufficient:\n/// - Fixed/min constraints take priority\n/// - Flex items shrink to zero before fixed items shrink\n/// - No negative sizes (saturating arithmetic)\npub const Constraint = union(enum) {\n    /// Exactly n cells.\n    length: u16,\n\n    /// At least n cells.\n    min: u16,\n\n    /// At most n cells.\n    max: u16,\n\n    /// Fraction of available space (numerator, denominator).\n    /// Example: ratio(1, 3) means 1/3 of available space.\n    ratio: Ratio,\n\n    /// Proportional share };\n\n    /// Create a length constraint (exactly n cells).\n    pub fn len(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .length = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a minimum constraint (at least n cells).\n    pub fn minSize(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .min = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a maximum constraint (at most n cells).\n    pub fn maxSize(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .max = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a ratio constraint (num/den of available space).\n    pub fn fractional(num: u16, den: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .ratio = .{ .num = num, .den = den } };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a flex constraint (proportional share).\n    pub fn flexible(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .flex = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Apply this constraint to resolve a concrete size given available space.\n    /// Returns the size this constraint requests, which may exceed available space.\n    /// The caller is responsible for ensuring the total doesn't exceed available.\n    pub fn apply(self: Constraint, available: u16) u16 {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .length => |n| n,\n            .min => |n| n,\n            .max => |n| @min(n, available),\n            .ratio => |r| blk: {\n                if (r.den == 0) break :blk 0;\n                const result = (@as(u32, available) * r.num) / r.den;\n                break :blk @intCast(@min(result, available));\n            },\n            .flex => available,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if two constraints are equal.\n    pub fn eql(self: Constraint, other: Constraint) bool {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .length => |n| other == .length and other.length == n,\n            .min => |n| other == .min and other.min == n,\n            .max => |n| other == .max and      .max => |n| {\n                sizes[i] = @min(n, total_space);\n                allocated += sizes[i];\n            },\n            .ratio => |r| {\n                if (r.den > 0) {\n                    const size: u16 = @intCast(@min(\n                        (@as(u32, total_space) * r.num) / r.den,\n                        total_space,\n                    ));\n                    sizes[i] Fixed constraints (length): Allocate exact requested size\n/// 2. Minimum constraints (min): Allocate at least requested size\n/// 3. Maximum constraints (max): Allocate at most requested size\n/// 4. Ratio constraints (ratio): Allocate fraction of total space\n/// 5. Flex constraints (flex): Distribute remaining space proportionally\n///\n/// When space is insufficient:\n/// - Fixed/min constraints take priority\n/// - Flex items shrink to zero before fixed items shrink\n/// - No negative sizes (saturating arithmetic)\npub const Constraint = union(enum) {\n    /// Exactly n cells.\n    length: u16,\n\n    /// At least n cells.\n    min: u16,\n\n    /// At most n cells.\n    max: u16,\n\n    /// Fraction of available space (numerator, denominator).\n    /// Example: ratio(1, 3) means 1/3 of available space.\n    ratio: Ratio,\n\n    /// Proportional share (like CSS flex-grow).\n    /// flex(1) and flex(1) = 50/50 split\n    /// flex(1) and flex(2) = 33/67 split\n    flex: u16,\n\n    pub const Ratio = struct {\n        num: u16,\n        den: u16,\n    };\n\n    /// Create a length constraint (exactly n cells).\n    pub fn len(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .length = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a minimum constraint (at least n cells).\n    pub fn minSize(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .min = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a maximum constraint (at most n cells).\n    pub fn maxSize(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .max = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a ratio constraint (num/den of available space).\n    pub fn fractional(num: u16, den: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .ratio = .{ .num = num, .den = den } };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a flex constraint (proportional share).\n    pub fn flexible(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .flex = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Apply this constraint to resolve a concrete size given available space.\n    /// Returns the size this constraint requests, which may exceed available space.\n    /// The caller is responsible for ensuring the total doesn't exceed available.\n    pub fn apply(self: Constraint, available: u16) u16 {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .length => |n| n,\n            .min => |n| n,\n            .max => |n| @min(n, available),\n            .ratio => |r| blk: {\n                if (r.den == 0) break :blk 0;\n                const result = (@as(u32, available) * r.num) / r.den;\n                break :blk @intCast(@min(result, available));\n            },\n            .flex => available,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if two constraints are equal.\n    pub fn eql(self: Constraint, other: Constraint) bool {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .length => |n| other == .length and other.length == n,\n            .min => |n| other == .min and other.min == n,\n            .max => |n| other == .max and other.max == n,\n            .ratio => |r| other == .ratio and other.ratio.num == r.num and other.ratio.den == r.den,\n            .flex => |n| other == .flex and other.flex == n,\n        };\n    }\n};\n\n// ============================================================\n// SANITY TESTS - Basic functionality\n// ============================================================\n\ntest \"sanity: Constraint.len creates correct constraint\" {\n    const c = Constraint.len(10);\n    try std.testing.expect(c == .length);\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(u16, 10), c.length);\n}\n\ntest };\n\n    /// Create a length constraint (exactly n cells).\n    pub fn len(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .length = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a minimum constraint (at least n cells).\n    pub fn minSize(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .min = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a maximum constraint (at most n cells).\n    pub fn maxSize(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .max = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a ratio constraint (num/den of available space).\n    pub fn fractional(num: u16, den: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .ratio = .{ .num = num, .den = den } };\n    }\n\n    /// Create a flex constraint (proportional share).\n    pub fn flexible(n: u16) Constraint {\n        return .{ .flex = n };\n    }\n\n    /// Apply this constraint to resolve a concrete size given available space.\n    /// Returns the size this constraint requests, which may exceed available space.\n    /// The caller is responsible for ensuring the total doesn't exceed available.\n    pub fn apply(self: Constraint, available: u16) u16 {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .length => |n| n,\n            .min => |n| n,\n            .max => |n| @min(n, available),\n available));\n            },\n            .flex => available,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Check if two constraints are equal.\n    pub fn eql(self: Constraint, other: Constraint) bool {\n        return switch (self) {\n            .length => |n| other == .length and other.length == n,\n            .min => |n| other == .min and other.min == n,\n            .max => |n| other == .max and other.max == n,\n            .ratio => |r| other == .ratio and other.ratio.num == r.num and other.ratio.den == r.den,\n            .flex => |n| other == .flex and other.flex == n,\n        };\n Fixed constraints (length): Allocate exact requested size\n/// 2. Minimum constraints (min): Allocate at least requested size\n/// 3. arithmetic)\n///\n/// Returns a bounded array of Rects matching the constraint count.\npub fn layout(\n    area: Rect,\n    direction: Direction,\n    constraints: []const Constraint,\n) BoundedRects {\n    const total_space: u16 = switch (direction) {\n        .horizontal => area.width,\n        .vertical => area.height,\n    };\n\n    var result = BoundedRects.init();\n\n    if (constraints.len |n| {\n                sizes[i] = n;\n                allocated += n;\n            },\n            .min => |n| {\n                sizes[i] = n;\n                allocated += n;\n            },\n         const size: u16 = @intCast(@min(\n                        (@as(u32, total_space) * r.num) / r.den,\n                        total_space,\n                    ));\n                    sizes[i] = size;\n                    allocated += size;\n                }\n            },\n            .flex => |weight| {\n                flex_total += weight;\n            },\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Phase 2: Distribute remaining space to flex items\n    if (flex_total > 0) {\n        const remaining: u16 = if (allocated >= total_space) 0 else total_space -| @as(u16, @intCast(allocated));\n
